<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Plain <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType" cert="low">statue base</rs> shaft (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.42</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.98</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.39</measure>), whose bottom surface has been hollowed out to form a basin with a drain hole. Top not visible.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p> <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face, which is chipped.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.036</measure>; diairetic dots on the initial <foreign lang="grc">Ι</foreign>; stop for abbreviation after <foreign lang="grc">ΚΛ</foreign> in l. 1; possible stops to either side of text in l. 7.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
 <head>Date</head>

<p>   <date notBefore="0167" notAfter="0200" cert="low">Late second century A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>; <rs type="criteria">nomenclature</rs>).</p></div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>

<ab><lb n="1"/><persName reg="Τιβέριος  Κλαύδιος  Ἀπολλώνιος  Αὐρηλιανός" full="yes" type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Τιβέριος" type="praenomen"><expan><abbr><unclear reason="damage">Τ</unclear>ι</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">βέριος</supplied></expan></name><name reg="Κλαύδιος"><expan><abbr>Κλ<orig><g type="stop"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αύδιος</supplied></expan></name>  <name reg="Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπο<unclear reason="damage">λλ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ώ</supplied><lb n="2" type="worddiv"/>νιος</name>  <name reg="Αὐρηλιανός">Αὐρηλια<lb n="3" type="worddiv"/>νὸς</name></persName>  <w lemma="ἀρχιερεύς">ἀρχιε  <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="4" type="worddiv"/>ρεὺς</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ἱερεύς">ἱε<lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>ρεὺς</w> <w lemma="διά">διὰ</w> <w lemma="βίος">βίου</w><lb n="6"/> <w lemma="θεός">θεοῦ</w> <persName type="divine" reg="Διόνυσος" full="yes"><name reg="Διόνυσος">Διονύ<lb n="7" type="worddiv"/><g type="scroll"/>σου</name></persName> <g type="leaf"/></ab>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Tiberius Claudius Apollonios Aurelianos high priest and priest for life of the god Dionysos <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up</supplied>.</p></div>

 <div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The purpose of the inscription/dedication is left unstated.</p>
</div>

<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p><rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">City, Village</rs>: re-used upside down as a well-head</rs> <rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs><rs type="lastLocation">Museum (1978)</rs>.</p>
</div>





